MBAZWANA - Five children aged between 5 and 15 years old have been critically injured in a collision involving a bus and a bakkie on their way to school on Monday morning.According to Arrive Alive the accident happened just after 7am on the R22 near Mbazwana, in north eastern Kwa-Zulu Natal.The driver and passengers of the bakkie were treated at the scene by paramedics from the KZN Health Department, before being transported to nearby hospitals.UPDATE: KZN bus crash kills 14Children who were transported by bus did not sustain any injuries during the crash.The exact cause of the accident is being investigated by the police.eNCA